<br>
::He nodded to Thanatos and then walked into the next room where Persephone lay still. He picked her up into his arms and walked with her over to his throne. He sat down upon his throne, with Persephone laying across his lap. He then took his amethyst tipped silver sceptor into his hand::<br>
<br>
::The crown upon his head began glowing a purple light, as well as the tip of his sceptor. Shortly thereafter, his eyes followed suit, glowing with dark purple light. They started glowing brighter and brighter, until the purple light engulfed the entire room, then eventually througout the palace. As the light continued to build, all the souls of the dead throughout Tartarus, the Elysian Fields included, began writhing in agony::<br>
<br>
::It seemed as though the entire palace was glowing, when for a brief moment, the entire purple light engulfed all of Tartarus in a seeming flash, when the flash occured all the souls fell over from the excrutiating pain. The light then subsided and eventually all back into his eyes. The souls then stood up, not experiencing any more pain::<br>
<br>
::Hades face seemed stern as he remarked in a cold voice aloud:: I am Hades! I am Tartarus! I am LORD OF THE UNDERWORLD!<br>
<br>
::Within the heads of each of the souls of the dead in Tartarus, is an ominous message:: ~That was a mere sampling of the pain which I can bring upon you, rebel against me again, and I will place that upon you for nothing short of an eternity~<br>
<br>
::A smirk then crossed Hades face as he sneered::<br>
<br>
